Olmert would return almost all occupied territories in exchange for peace
The chairman of the provisional Israeli government, Ehud Olmert, spoke out in favour of the return of virtually all territories occupied in 1967, including Jordan, East Jerusalem and the Golan Heights, if peace could be concluded with Palestine and Syria in exchange.
He emphasized this in an interview, which was printed on Monday by the daily Jediot Achronot.
