Questions about the accident: Are stewards illegal on the bus?
The law does not know her, in a long-distance bus it is not permitted to walk around
In connection with the tragic accident of a bus operated by the Student Agency near Padua in Italy, the question arises whether stewards and travellers are allowed to walk back and forth in the bus while travelling.
"If we want to comply strictly and formally with the law, the activity of a steward is contrary to the law on road transport," said Karel Hanzelka, spokesman for the Ministry of Transport.
The accident, in which a twenty-two-year-old stewardess was killed last week, was probably caused by the driver of the truck crossing the way of the bus.
At this moment, the young woman was sitting next to the driver, in the least safe place in the car, even though she had two more seats at her disposal.
However, a bus can also have an accident or sharply slow down at the moment when the steward carries out coffee or newspapers.
It also plays a role whether the bus is equipped with standing places after the vehicle letter.
If this is not provided for in the bus, the passengers must sit.
Student Agency's long-distance coaches have no standing space, as confirmed by the director of the company, Radim Jančura, opposite Aktuálně.cz.
"We discussed this with the ministry, and this did not agree to the movement of travellers at first.
Later this was withdrawn, and we reached a consensus that travellers may go to the toilet while driving if they have their seat," he said.
The law doesn't know a steward
"There is no clear legal interpretation of the role of a steward - no legislation describes this role.
However, there is no legislation prohibiting the carrier from providing services.
The law on road transport only knows the concept of vehicle attendants, but its rights and obligations do not define them," adds the spokesman of the Hanzelka Ministry.
The director of the Department of Road Vehicles of the Ministry of Transport Josef Pokorný, on the other hand, believes that the law covers this problem retrospectively.
"It depends on whether the bus in the product registration also has standing places.
That's all," he emphasizes.
Buses are divided into city buses, where there are standing spaces and the maximum speed is limited, buses with standing spaces and a higher permitted speed, and coaches with no standing spaces with the highest permitted speed and seats equipped with safety belts.
As in the plane, the expert says
The BESIP specialist in road safety Jaroslav Hořín sees no fundamental problem in the movement of stewards on board a bus.
"There are not many risks associated with a liquid way of driving, the situation is comparable to the service on board an aircraft.
Again, it is not certain when turbulence is coming, and the stewardess can bump his head."
"However, if a bus is sharp, then of course the laws of physics apply.
Just like a city bus or a tram.
The safety of the stewards must be clarified by internal regulations," he says, and also believes that this problem will not be fully resolved from the point of view of the law.
Jančura is ready to cancel the services
Student Agency is the only bus company offering Stewards services.
The company employs about two hundred people in this function.
Even after the accident, the director does not consider her profession to be risky.
"But as soon as I get the impression that the steward's profession is risky, I will delete it.
Coffee and newspapers can be provided to travellers when boarding.
That would also reduce costs," he says.
As an interest in safety, the director of Asiana Alexej Litvin explains the lack of stewards in his buses. However, his company operates only a fraction of lines compared to Student Agency.
"We don't have stewardesses, we'll fight them right from the start.
Sooner or later this ends with some fatal accident," he had said for Týden.cz not quite a year ago.
That was an incredible tragedy
In the accident of a regular bus to Naples, a young stewardess from the Pilsen region, who had worked for the company for two years, was injured.
The Slovenian truck had probably turned off without blinking from the stand strip and had blocked the bus's journey.
The driver of the bus tried to avoid by a sharp maneuver, but colliding with the right front part with the truck.
Jančura denies that the two places for the stewards were sold.
"These places cannot be reserved for long-distance connections, they are blocked."
Company wants to sue truck drivers.
With compensation for the young woman's family, the agency will not wait for the court ruling, but it also expects financial compensation from the culprit.
A change of laws?
Not in sight
A more detailed regulation of the movement of stewards on board a bus could bring about a legal regulation on which a thirty-strong team of experts at the Ministry of Transport has been working for over a year.
"This, however, has not yet reached a concrete conclusion.
Buses are also not necessarily on the agenda, rather the point system, the top speed on the motorway and the use of mobile phones when driving," says Hořín.
"The Ministry of Transport does not consider the stewards' activities to be something that could significantly endanger the safety of travellers," says Hanzelka, with the control of the safety of buses being the competence of the police and the health and safety authorities.
