The drivers, who can become relapsed because of the alcohol level, will have to install the 'Alcolock'.
The authority orders that the driver, who had three official penalties for the alcohol level, install this system in his car, which forbids him to start the car in drunken condition. If he is alcoholic, the car will not start.
The initiative was announced last month in June and is already part of the report of the Attorney General's Office. According to them, it is a pilot project that will last for a year.
The purpose is to re-socialize the driver, which is why he gets a course for re-education of traffic behaviour.
