According to statistics, between 30-75% of drivers, who were reported more than once because of driving under the influence of alcohol, were back at the wheel.
The 'alcolock' would prevent this because it is a system connected to the car, it measures the alcohol content in the exhaled air and prevents car start when the driver has made alcohol test; or if an alcohol concentration is detected that is higher than allowed.
It costs more than 1 000 euros, the costs are borne by the person who imposes the penalty.
In this context, a study conducted in the US in 2007 showed that cars equipped with these devices prevent up to 65% of the regulatory violations in the first year after its introduction.
Spain is expected to save 115 lives a year.
The measure is limited to administrative sanctions for two reasons: to tackle this behaviour before it becomes a criminal offence.
And in order to facilitate its implementation, a legal reform can be carried out in the ordinary way, and yet a reform of the Basic Law is required, which is necessary for the prosecution process.
The device is not yet available on the Spanish markets, even though it has already been installed in some commercial vehicles and public transport vehicles.
