Some children talk at night
I don't mean those who wake up and tell us something that happened the day before, but the children who talk during sleep.
When it happens to you for the first time, in the best case you will be terrified, but in reality it has no meaning.
This is a positive sleep disorder called speaking in sleep.
It is quite common, especially among children and adolescents.
Certainly, more than one of you was told that you spoke at night.
This phenomenon may occur occasionally (once in life, for example, during high fever), or regularly (every day, once a week, once a month), the next day the child cannot remember anything.
There is not a single reason that causes this phenomenon.
Often connections with other phenomena in sleep are sought, such as nightmares, panic anxiety at night, Enuresis noctura (bedwetting at night), speaking in sleep, but there is no reason for it.
As we mentioned earlier, it can be due to very high fiber, stress situations or excessive stress.
In any case, this is a little researched phenomenon.
The frequency with which it occurs is very variable.
It may be that one speaks, whispers or it can be quite the opposite in individual words (scream, crying, long discussions ).
In cases where the expression is very intense, it is recommended to observe the child and to seek advice from a specialist in order to check whether there is a problem, which causes fear and thus arises.
We have said that it is a positive disorder, so it is not treated, be it, it is associated with another sleep disorder that can be treated (for example, with sleep apnea or with stress).
What you can do is perform a series of simple preventive measures:
Try not to excite the child before sleeping.
So choose quiet game for the child and avoid stressful TV programs that are terrible and something too wild.
The nervous children who are recommended to relax can use relaxation methods to help them get some inner peace.
This helps the child to sleep quietly.
When speaking occurs in sleep, try to keep quiet.
